results.name: An L-tile is a 2 X 2 square with the upper 1 X 1 subsquare removed; no rotations are allowed. a(n) = number of tilings of a 4 X n rectangle using tiles that are either 1 X 1 squares or L-tiles.
link: E. Deutsch, Counting tilings with L-tiles and squares, Problem 10877, Amer. Math. Monthly, 110 (March 2003), 245-246.
